From 0000000000000000000000000000000000000000 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Gaggery Tsai <gaggery.tsai@intel.com>
Date: Tue, 8 Apr 2026 15:00:00 -0700
Subject: [PATCH] drm/i915/psr: Allow PSR with VRR on Panther Lake

The blanket VRR rejection in _psr_compute_config() prevents PSR2
from coexisting with VRR on all platforms. On Panther Lake (PTL,
DISPLAY_VER 30), PSR2 + VRR has been tested and works correctly.

The existing Wa_16011303918 in intel_psr2_config_valid() already
handles the Alderlake-P stepping-specific VRR incompatibility.

Remove the blanket check to allow PSR2 + VRR on platforms where
no specific workaround applies.

Signed-off-by: Gaggery Tsai <gaggery.tsai@intel.com>
---
diff --git a/drivers/gpu/drm/i915/display/intel_psr.c b/drivers/gpu/drm/i915/display/intel_psr.c
index 197c238..242077f 100644
--- a/drivers/gpu/drm/i915/display/intel_psr.c
+++ b/drivers/gpu/drm/i915/display/intel_psr.c
@@ -1714,12 +1714,6 @@ static bool _psr_compute_config(struct intel_dp *intel_dp,
 	if (!CAN_PSR(intel_dp) || !display->params.enable_psr)
 		return false;
 
-	/*
-	 * Currently PSR doesn't work reliably with VRR enabled.
-	 */
-	if (crtc_state->vrr.enable)
-		return false;
-
 	entry_setup_frames = intel_psr_entry_setup_frames(intel_dp, conn_state, adjusted_mode);
 
 	if (entry_setup_frames >= 0) {
